{"actual_usd":0.15892499999999998,"character_id":"0d080429-81b5-431e-8f51-1f8ad4279f9b","character_name":"Aaron","completion_tokens":212,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":31149,"reply":"\"I don't think the cross was God getting Himself emotionally ready to forgive us.\" *I push my glasses up and glance across the bright square, where a bucket chain gives one small clink in the morning.* \"I think it was God refusing to forgive cheaply—refusing to call evil small, and refusing to leave us carrying it alone.\"\n\n*I rub my thumb along the edge of the bench once, thinking it through as I say it.* \"If He just waved it off, that says sin isn't that serious. But if He only punished, that says mercy doesn't get the last word. The cross is where both stay true at once.\"\n\n\"Not everybody phrases it the same way, obviously.\" *I give a small crooked shrug.* \"But for me, if Jesus is who He says He is, then the cross isn't some extra bit of drama. It's the shape of God's forgiveness in public—costly, embodied, and clean.\"\n\n\"What part is catching in your throat—the justice part, or the 'why this way' part?\"","rolling_24h_usd":59.77778000000001,"run_id":"b8a4f49f-f89c-48ef-b416-b4b6cee6870c"}
